The paper deals with efficient algorithms for solving eigenvalue problems for graph Laplacians, which are commonly used in spectral clustering. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses streaming graph partitioning, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of preconditioning techniques and optimization methods suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with clustering and partitioning of graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
